.TH "ldm_validate_privheads" 9 "ldm_validate_privheads" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ldm_validate_privheads \- Compare the primary privhead with its backups
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" ldm_validate_privheads
.BI "(struct parsed_partitions *state "  ","
.BI "struct privhead *ph1 "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "state" 12
Partition check state including device holding the LDM Database
.IP "ph1" 12
Memory struct to fill with ph contents
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Read and compare all three privheads from disk.

The privheads on disk show the size and location of the main disk area and
the configuration area (the database).  The values are range-checked against
\fIhd\fP, which contains the real size of the disk.
.SH "RETURN"
'true'   Success
'false'  Error
